					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Original schematics has been updated. Now it limits the CHR area to the lower 16KB instead of the lower 32KB, and the upper 48KB should work just like it does on a real NES when accessed.
<br />
<br />I also added a XOR-OR based comparator for the addres decoder if the design is to be put on an ISA card. It would also be possible to use a 4-bit demultiplexer with a 16*2 pin-connector and a jumper, however 4-bit demultiplexers are not as common as theit 3-bit counterparts.
<br />
<br />I do not have any kind of flashcartridge, and I don't want to sacrifice one of my games, so the bootloader solution is at the moment out of question.</div>

